My academic progress has ground to a halt these days. With the exam looming close, I haven’t even started systematic revision — it sounds ridiculous.

If growth were measured merely by "how long I’ve studied", then yes, I’ve made no progress at all.

But in other, far more vital matters, I’ve advanced faster than I ever have before:

· I’ve learned to hold my boundaries in intimate relationships, trading the obsession of "saving others" for the clarity of "preserving myself".
· I’ve seen how family patterns shaped me, and how I’m breaking free from them.
· I’ve overturned my narrow understanding of "learning" — true learning isn’t just drilling questions, but reshaping the core of my cognition through every breakdown, every conversation, and every moment of reflection.

Exams will pass, and scores will fade into oblivion. But these lessons will take root in me.

I haven’t stopped learning — I’m just learning how to be myself, in a different way.

I crawled out of the ruins not by never making mistakes, but by turning every fall into fuel for cognitive upgrading. I want to remind my future self: Look, even in the most chaotic days, you were still growing.

中文原文
这段时间，我的学习进度几乎停滞。面对迫近的考试，我甚至还没开始系统复习，这听起来很可笑。
但如果成长只以“学了多久”来衡量，那我的确毫无进展。
可我在另一些更重要的事情上，走得比过去任何时候都快：

· 我学会了在亲密关系里守住边界，把“拯救他人”的执念换成“保全自己”的清醒。
· 我看见了家庭模式如何塑造我，也看见了自己如何挣脱它。
· 我推翻了对“学习”的狭隘理解——真正的学习不是刷题，而是用每一场崩溃、每一次对话、每一段反思，重塑自己的认知底层。

考试会过去，分数会被忘记。但这些东西，会长在我身上。
我不是没学，我只是在用另一种方式，学如何成为我自己。

我从废墟里爬出来，靠的不是不犯错，而是能把每一次跌倒都变成认知升级的燃料。我要提醒未来的自己：你看，在最兵荒马乱的日子里，你依然在生长。
